# Exercise 004 - First OpenShift database deployment

1) As user developer create a project named my-first-project;

2) Create a new application named my-first-application that will deploy the
   mysql container with these environment variable passed on the command line:
   - MYSQL_USER=user
   - MYSQL_PASSWORD=pass
   - MYSQL_DATABASE=testdb

3) Explore the status of your deployment;

4) Using oc port-forward expose locally the 3306 port from the pod that is
   running;

5) Check that the service is accessible;

6) Delete my-first-project;

BONUS) Check that the mysql container image is now part of the OpenShift
       registry;
